NUMBER 13
NAME Sacred Oak
DAY_LIGHT
FOREST
*DESCRIPTION_START
The first thing you notice here is a majestic silver oak tree that dominates
the area. It's canopy dwarfs all others near it, and you sense a feeling of
holiness that prevades the glade that can't easily be explained.
A path leads away.
*DESCRIPTION_END
;-----knot--------
ITEM 0 1436
IFVERB PRAY -1
	IFVAR FLAG1 = 1
		ECHO PLAYER You are already praying.
	ENDIF
	IFVAR FLAG1 ! 1
		ECHO PLAYER You begin to chant a sacred mantra.
		ECHO OTHERS %N begins to chant the sacred mantra.
		EQUAL FLAG1 1
		ADD VOICES 1
		IFVAR VOICES < 3
			ECHO PLAYER You sense the power of goodness growing stronger, but you realize that more voices are needed.
		ENDIF
		IFVAR VOICES = 3
			ECHO ALL As your voices lift in unison to the goodness in the universe, the knothole begins to shimmer. You know instinctively that the tree has the power to destroy evil.
		ENDIF
		PLREVENT 8
		CONTPLREVENT
		ECHO PLAYER You stop chanting.
		ECHO OTHERS %N stops chanting.
		SUB VOICES 1
		EQUAL FLAG1 0
	ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB2 PUT 0
	CLEARVERB
	IFVAR VOICES >= 3
		REMOVEITEM -1
		ECHO ALL As %n places the item in the knothole, there is a bright flash of light and it disappears!%c%cA great weight lifts from your heart.
	ENDIF
	IFVAR VOICES < 3
		ECHO ALL The tree does not have enough power at the moment.
	ENDIF
ENDIF
;-----path out------
ITEM 1 74
IFVERB GO 1
	CLEARVERB
	IFVAR FLAG1 = 1
		ECHO PLAYER You are still chanting
	ENDIF
	IFVAR FLAG1 = 0
		ECHO PLAYER You walk away from the tree.
		ECHO OTHERS %N goes away.
		MOVE 569
		AFFECT 569
		ECHO OTHERS %N approaches from the direction of the sacred oak tree.
		AFFECT 13
	ENDIF
ENDIF
;--------tree-------
ITEM 2 229 ADJ1=1123 ADJ2=292 ADJ3=216
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 2
The branches of the sacred oak splay out over the sky as you look up into them.
Urimar oozes from under the tree bark forming ochre rivulets down the trunk.
There is a large knothole in one side of the tree.  
*DESCRIPTION_END
IFPREVERB HUG 2
	CLEARVERB
	IFVAR ORG = 15
		ECHO PLAYER You hug the rough bark of the silver oak feeling blessed.
		ECHO OTHERS %N smiles and closes %h eyes as %s hugs the majestic oak.
		SPELL 347 100
	ELSE
		ECHO PLAYER You hug the oak but feel no real connection.
		ECHO OTHERS %N hugs the oak.
	ENDIF
ENDIF
