NUMBER 568
NAME Grasslands
PLAIN
DAY_LIGHT
*DESCRIPTION_START
A magnificent pair of oak trees guards the entrance to a beautiful looking
grove of trees. Their trunks have a golden hue and are entwined by thick, green
vines dotted with attractive red and yellow flowers. The sounds and smells of
nature in all its glory emanate from within the grove. Birds sing lilting,
melodic tunes, and fragrant flowers in full bloom make the copse come alive
with nature's essence. A boulder with some writing on it marks a path leading
within.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT W 564
EXIT N 1470
;-------path------
ITEM 0 74 VAL2=569
IFVERB GO 0
	IFVAR ALIGN <= -1
		ECHO PLAYER The forces of nature align to force you away from the grove.
		ECHO OTHERS %N tried to enter the grove but is thrown back by some unseen source.
	ENDIF
	IFVAR ALIGN > -1
		ECHO PLAYER You enter the grove.
		ECHO OTHERS %N enters the grove.
		MOVE 569
		AFFECT 569
		ECHO OTHERS %N arrives.
		AFFECT 568
		CLEARVERB
	ENDIF
	CLEARVERB
ENDIF
