NUMBER 570
NAME Forester's Guild, meadow
FOREST
DAY_LIGHT
*DESCRIPTION_START
At the center of the grove is a gently rolling meadow dotted with wild
flowers. People of all races train in the various skills needed to protect
and preserve nature. At the south end of the meadow, students listen as
their teacher speaks of different flora and fauna. Another group studies
the lifecycles of various animals, examining some of the season's newborns.
The sounds of swords clashing and the twanging of bowstrings can be heard
emanating from further south. A short ways northwest of here, a majestic
silver oak reaches for the sky. A sense of peaceful harmony can be felt
from the path leading to the meeting area. To the east the sights, sounds
and smells of craftsmen engaged in their work can be sensed. A large and
weathered maple sits at the eastern edge of the meadow. At the base of
the maple is a door.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT W 569
EXIT E 2268
EXIT S 2269
