NUMBER 2267
NAME Foresters Guild, meeting ground
FOREST
DAY_LIGHT
*DESCRIPTION_START
A circle of healthy oaks and mirmachs stand guard around this gentle glade.
Polished wooden benches have been placed around a small fire pit in the
center of the glade, the sheen of the wood complementing the glittering
ring of rocks encircling the fire pit. The leaves of the mighty trees gently
rustle in the wind, adding a pleasant harmony to the gentle song of the
various birds that nest within the upper branches of the oaks and mirmachs.
*DESCRIPTION_END
;----------path----------
ITEM 0 80 VAL2=570
;----------pit-----------
ITEM 1 1398 ADJ1=126
VARIABLE askin
IFPREVERB GO 1
	CLEARVERB
    	ECHO PLAYER Why would you want to go there?
ENDIF
IFPREVERB LOOK 1
  CLEARVERB
   IFVAR askin = 0
     ECHO PLAYER Tiny, uncut gems sparkle within each of the rocks that surround the small fire pit.
     ECHO OTHERS %N looks at the fire pit.
   ENDIF
    IFVAR askin = 1
      ECHO PLAYER The blazing fire causes the circle of rocks to glimmer with a magical light that illuminates the surrounding trees in vibrant, dazzling lights.
      ECHO OTHERS %N looks into the blazing fire.
    ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB LIGHT 1
  CLEARVERB
   IFVAR askin = 1
     ECHO PLAYER The fire is already lit.
     ECHO OTHERS %N, for some reason, throws another match onto the fire.
   ENDIF
    IFVAR askin = 0
      ECHO PLAYER You carefully light a fire in the pit.
      ECHO OTHERS %N carefully lights a fire in the pit.
      EQUAL askin 1
    ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB EXTINGUISH 1
  CLEARVERB
   IFVAR askin = 0
     ECHO PLAYER There is no fire in the pit at the moment.
     ECHO OTHERS %N makes a great show of trying to put out the non-existent fire in the pit.
   ENDIF
    IFVAR askin = 1
      ECHO PLAYER Taking great care so as not to cause sparks you extinguish the blazing fire.
      ECHO OTHERS %N carefully extinguishes the flames in the pit.
      EQUAL askin 0
    ENDIF
ENDIF
;----------bench---------
ITEM 2 339 ADJ1=241 ADJ2=355
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 2
The polished wooden benches show each intricate whorl within the wood they
have been made from. Their slight vibrating is due to the wood still being
alive. An intricate process that takes a portion of wood from a tree and
still keeps both wood and tree alive has been used in making these benches.
*DESCRIPTION_END
;----------ucantsee------
ITEM 9 693
CALL 33
;-----------------------------------
IFENTRY
  IFVAR askin = 1
    ECHO PLAYER As you enter you notice that a fire has been lit in the pit. Its light and warmth adding to the air of pleasantness and harmony that is in the air.
  ENDIF
ENDIF
IFVERB LISTEN -1
  IFVAR askin = 0
    ECHO PLAYER The delightful song of the birds fills your ears.
    ECHO OTHERS %N smiles pleasantly as %s listens to the singing of the birds.
  ENDIF
   IFVAR askin = 1
     ECHO PLAYER The gentle crackling of flames from the blazing fire fills the glade.
     ECHO OTHERS %N listens to the gentle crackling of the fire.
   ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB LAY -1
    CLEARVERB
    ECHO PLAYER You flop down in the soft fragrant grass and feel immediately relaxed and rested.
    ECHO OTHERS %N seems very relaxed as %s reclines on the fragrant grass and yawns.
    POSITION LAY
    SPELL 334 100
    SPELL 217 100
ENDIF
IFPREVERB SIT -1
    CLEARVERB
    ECHO PLAYER As you sit on the bench the living wood molds to your form, easing your tired muscles with the soothing presence of nature.
    ECHO OTHERS %N eases onto one of the benches with a relaxed sigh.
    POSITION SIT
ENDIF
