NUMBER 2268
NAME Foresters, crafts area
OUTDOOR_OTHER
DAY_LIGHT
*DESCRIPTION_START
The surrounding flora has been cleared away in this bustling place to make
room for the craftsmen of the Foresters Guild. Numerous members are involved
in the task of creating beautiful, and useful, items from the materials that
only nature's bounty can provide. The clash of hammer upon anvil resounds
from under the awning of the Trockmin brothers, competing with the bellowing
voice of Nedral Trockmin as he attempts to teach the finer points of mining
to an eager group of students. Under another awning one can hear the clack and
rattle of a loom. Torm the brewer has, as always, a new batch of ale for you to
taste test. Inside a small shed on the far side of the clearing is the shop of
Qounvar Martham, master bow maker. 
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT W 570
